post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_33963794_33964384_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 0.8823529411764706, "section_id": 6689}}, "n3337": {"so_33963794_33964384_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 0.8823529411764706, "section_id": 6444}}, "n4659": {"so_33963794_33964384_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 0.8823529411764706, "section_id": 8164}}}, "33963794": {"ViewCount": "34", "Body": "<p>However, you can define a function in a friend declaration. <strong>The class must be a non-local class, function, the function name must be unqualified, and the function has namespace scope.</strong> The following example demonstrates this: </p>\n<pre><code>class A { void g(); };\n\nvoid z() {\nclass B { // friend void f() { }; }; \n} \n\nclass C { // friend void A::g() { } \nfriend void h() { } \n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>Though I understood what's meant by <code>The class must be a non-local class</code> but after that comma it eludes me or that function word alone surround by comma is  typo?. What exactly whole para means word for word I mean. Thanks</p>\n<p>P.S Above para is stolen from ibm C++ reference -&gt; <a href=\"https://www-01.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/ssw_ibm_i_72/rzarg/cplr042.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www-01.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/ssw_ibm_i_72/rzarg/cplr042.htm</a></p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "33964384", "Title": "Need help understanding a paragraph pertaining to friend declaration", "CreationDate": "2015-11-27T19:31:49.223", "Id": "33963794", "CommentCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2015-11-27T20:45:57.903", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "4882052", "Tags": "<c++><friend>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "33964384": {"Id": "33964384", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Here's the wording from C++14 standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_33963794_33964384_0\"><strong>[class.friend]/6</strong> A function can be defined in a friend declaration of a class if and only if the class is a non-local class (9.8), the function name is unqualified, and the function has namespace scope. [ <em>Example:</em></p>\n<pre><code>class M {\n  friend void f() { } // definition of global f, a friend of M,\n                      // not the definition of a member function\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p id=\"so_33963794_33964384_1\">\u2014 <em>end example</em> ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "1670129", "LastActivityDate": "2015-11-27T20:45:57.903", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2015-11-27T20:22:41.887", "ParentId": "33963794", "CommentCount": "7", "OwnerUserId": "1670129", "LastEditDate": "2015-11-27T20:45:57.903"}});